
                                                        +-------+
                                                        |  .BM  |
                                                        +-------+

BOTTOM MARGIN  specifies the number of  lines to be  left between
the bottom of the output page and the bottom of the text area.

     +-------+---------------------------------------------+
     |       |                                             |
     |  .BM  |    <<.U+>6<.U->|m|+m|-m>                              |<.NORMAL>
     |       |                                             |
     +-------+---------------------------------------------+

<.B+><<.U+>6<.U->|m>:  <.B->At the  bottom of all subsequent  output pages (including<.NORMAL>
   the current page),  <.U+>m<.U-> <.U->lines will  appear between the bottom of<.NORMAL>
   the text area and the physical bottom of the page.Ä
<.B+><+m|-m>:  <.B->this value  will be added algebraically  to the current<.NORMAL>
   bottom margin  value,  so long as  the resulting value  is not
   negative.

This control  word causes a  break.   Unless  otherwise specified
<.U+>m<.U-> <.U->= 6 will be in effect.   If used without an operand,  the value<.NORMAL>
of the BMargin  option will be taken,  normally  6.   Any footing
lines will appear within these <.U+>m<.U-> <.U->lines.Å If the Footing Margin is<.NORMAL>
<.U+>fm<.U->, the Footing Space is <.U+>fs<.U->,  and the Bottom Margin <.U+>bm<.U->,  then the<.NORMAL>
bottom of each page will contain:
(1) <.U+>fm<.U-> <.U->blank lines,<.NORMAL>
(2) the <.U+>fs<.U-> <.U->footing lines,<.NORMAL>
(3) <.U+>bm<.U-> <.U->- <.U+>fm<.U-> <.U->- <.U+>fs<.U-> <.U->blank lines.<.NORMAL>

The FOOTING MARGIN plus FOOTING SPACE must always be less than or
equal to the BOTTOM MARGIN.

_____________________

Ä Footnotes are printed in the text area.

Å Do not confuse  these with footnote lines.    Footing lines are
  those "bottom title" lines defined by the ".BT",  ".EB",  ".OB"
  and ".RT BOTTOM"  control words,  and  are printed in  the area
  defined by ".FS".

